#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:1
msgid "American Audio VMS4/4.1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:4
msgid ""
"The original VMS4 has problems with sound quality. The microphone input "
"impedance is off and the output volume is low. The VMS4.1 is the same "
"controller, except that those hardware issues have been fixed. The Traktor "
"edition has different labels on some buttons & knobs, but it’s otherwise the"
" same hardware as the VMS4.1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:10
msgid "[VMS4](http://www.adj.com/vms4)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:11
msgid "[VMS4.1](http://www.adj.com/vms4-1)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:12
msgid "[VMS4.1 Traktor edition](http://www.adj.com/vms4-1-traktor)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:16
msgid "Setup"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:20
msgid ""
"Mixxx expects the VMS4 to be set to “Post EQ” mode for best sound quality. "
"Do this by holding down the Headphone Cue button on Midilog 4 while powering"
" on the unit. You only need to do this once. (Each time you do, it changes "
"the mode back and forth.) Consult the [user "
"manual](https://web.archive.org/web/20220727170646/intranet.americandj.com/ItemRelatedFiles/8347/vms4.pdf)"
" for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:27
msgid ""
"To check the status of this in Linux, at a console, issue the command "
"``lsusb -v|grep 'iSerial\\|iProduct'`` and look at the serial number under "
"the VMS4 device per the instructions in the user manual. As of this writing,"
" the leading digit should be **1**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:32
msgid "Make sure the VMS4 is off"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:33
msgid "Slide the switch on the front of the VMS4 to “8 OUT”"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:35
msgid ""
"If you’re using vinyl control or aux devices (or Mixxx 1.11 & below) set the"
" switch to “4 OUT” for 2-deck output and 2-deck input"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:39
msgid "Turn on the unit (and plug in the USB cable if you haven’t yet)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:40
msgid "Start Mixxx"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:41
msgid "Open Preferences"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:42
msgid "Click Sound Hardware. In the right pane:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:44
msgid "Set the sample rate to **44100Hz**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:45
msgid "Set the Main output to **None**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:46
msgid "Set the Headphone output to **None**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:47
msgid ""
"Set the Deck 1 output to the **VMS4** device and **Channel 3-4** (may show "
"as “USB Audio Device” on Windows)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:49
msgid "Set the Deck 2 output to the **VMS4** device and **Channel 5-6**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:50
msgid "Set the Deck 3 output to the **VMS4** device and **Channel 1-2**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:51
msgid "Set the Deck 4 output to the **VMS4** device and **Channel 7-8**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:53
msgid ""
"If you’re using 4 OUT mode, (for vinyl control/aux input or Mixxx 1.11 & "
"below):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:56
msgid "Set the Deck 1 output to the **VMS4** device and **Channel 1-2**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:58
msgid "Set the Deck 2 output to the **VMS4** device and **Channel 3-4**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:60
msgid ""
"For vinyl control, set the Vinyl Control 1 input to the **VMS4** device and "
"**Channel 1-2**, connect a turntable to Midilog 1, and set it to Analog."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:63
msgid ""
"For vinyl control, set the Vinyl Control 2 input to the **VMS4** device and "
"**Channel 3-4**, connect a turntable to Midilog 4, and set it to Analog."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:67
msgid ""
"Plug your headphones into the VMS4’s jack on the front. You will use the "
"VMS4’s CUE buttons and knobs for headphone control."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:69
msgid "Still in the Preferences, expand “Controllers” on the left"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:70
msgid ""
"Select the “VMS4 MIDI” device (may show as “USB Audio Device” on Windows)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:73
msgid ""
"Do not choose the the HID one. That’s for the little mouse pad and button "
"area."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:76
msgid "Click the Enable checkbox in the right pane"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:77
msgid ""
"Click the drop-down and choose the {guilabel}`American Audio VMS4` preset"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:78
msgid ""
"Click OK and the controller should light up. (In 1.9.x, the controller will "
"light up when you load a track to a deck.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:80
msgid "Continue reading below to know how everything is mapped"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:82
msgid "Direct deck output implications"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:85
msgid ""
"This setup uses direct deck outputs because mixing takes place in the VMS4 "
"hardware. The down side to this is that you won’t be able to use Mixxx "
"features that play to Main or Cue buses like the Preview Deck or Samplers. "
"Using these features with a hardware + MIDI mixer like the VMS4 is not "
"really feasible unless you used a separate sound interface or controlled "
"Mixxx’s internal mixer another way."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:92
msgid "Control"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:95
msgid "This guide explains how the VMS4 is mapped by default in Mixxx."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:97
msgid ""
"**Easy customization:** We have provided the following customization "
"variables at the top of the script you can set to your liking:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:100
msgid ""
"**RateRanges**: Set the pitch slider range each time you toggle it with "
"Shift+Sync."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:103
msgid ""
"Just open the ``midi/American-Audio-VMS4-scripts.js`` file in your favorite "
"text editor (Wordpad works too) and you’ll see these variables right near "
"the top. Edit & save, then restart Mixxx and enjoy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:107
msgid "Deck controls"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:111
msgid ""
"There are a number of different face plates in the wild so these images and "
"control descriptions may not exactly match yours. The locations of the "
"controls are the key things to pay attention to."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:115
msgid ""
"*The controls are the same on both sides of the controller. The left side "
"controls Deck 1 and the right side controls Deck 2.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:118
msgid ""
"**Sync/Range** button - Changes the BPM of this deck to match that of the "
"other. When shifted, toggles the pitch slider range. (See top of page to "
"customize.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:121
msgid ""
"**Hot cue buttons** - Press to set or recall a hot cue. The buttons light up"
" red when one is set. Hold Shift and press to access hot cues 5-8. (The "
"buttons light up blue for these.) Hold Vinyl and press to delete the cue. "
"(Note: there is a bug in some firmware versions that causes hot cues 5 and 6"
" to be deleted simultaneously.) the cue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:128
msgid "**Pitch Bend +/-**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:129
msgid ""
"Momentarily speeds up or slows down the deck while the button is held down."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:131
msgid ""
"Hold Shift and press to adjust the key (pitch) of the song (independent of "
"the tempo.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:132
msgid "**Loop In** - Set the in point of a loop"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:133
msgid "**Loop Out** - Set the out point of a loop"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:134
msgid ""
"**Reloop** - Toggle a previously-set loop. Lights red when a loop is active."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:136
msgid ""
"**Loop/Smart** Start a 4-beat loop. Hold Shift and press to toggle "
"quantization (locking to the nearest beat.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:138
msgid ""
"**Vinyl/Keylock** - *(Does nothing on its own when un-shifted at the "
"moment.)* When shifted, toggles key lock."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:140
msgid ""
"**<< Search/ /2** - Fast-rewind Hold Shift and press to halve the current "
"loop length"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:142
msgid ""
"**Search >>/ \\*2** - Fast-forward Hold Shift and press to double the "
"current loop length"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:144
msgid ""
"**Touch strip** Scroll through the respective Library panes. (Left for the "
"folders/crates list, right for the track list.) Hold Shift and touch:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:148
msgid ""
"to affect the Dry/Wet knob on the respective effect unit while the deck is "
"playing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:149
msgid "for Needle drop - search through the track while the deck is stopped"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:151
msgid ""
"**Wheel** Move the wheel while touching the top to scratch the current track"
" like a vinyl record Move the wheel without touching the top (so on the "
"sides) to perform a temporary pitch bend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:154
msgid ""
"**CUE** - Operates according to the Cue mode set in Mixxx's preferences Hold"
" Shift and press to play immediately from the cue point (known as Cue+Play "
"or CUP.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:156
msgid ""
"**Play** - Press to toggle deck playback Hold Shift and press to set this "
"deck as the leader for syncing with another"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:158
msgid "**Pause** - Stops the deck playback"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:160
msgid "Effects section"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:163
msgid ""
"The left side controls effect unit 1 and the right side controls effect unit"
" 2."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:166
msgid "**Select knob**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:167
msgid "Rotate to choose the effect chain preset"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:168
msgid "Press to toggle whether the effect unit is on or not"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:170
msgid "**Control knob**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:171
msgid "Adjusts the wet/dry ratio"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:172
msgid ""
"When Parameter is on, this becomes the Wonder Knob, adjusting all effect "
"parameters at once"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:175
msgid ""
"**On/Off** - Toggles the effect for the deck matching the effect unit number"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:177
msgid "**Parameter** - Toggles what the above Control knob adjusts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:179
msgid "Sample section"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:182
msgid ""
"The left side of the controller controls Sampler 1, and the right, Sampler "
"2."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:185
msgid ""
"**Select knob** Rotate to move the highlight in the library. Press to load "
"the currently highlighted track into the sampler. Hold Shift and press to "
"eject the current track from the sampler (when the sampler is not playing.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:190
msgid "**Volume knob** - Adjusts the volume of the sampler"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:191
msgid ""
"**Play** Press to play the sample from the beginning. Press while playing "
"for a stutter-play effect (play again from the beginning.) Hold Shift and "
"press to stop playing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:195
msgid "**Rec** - *Currently does nothing*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:197
msgid "Mixer controls"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:200
msgid ""
"The volume sliders don’t control the ones in Mixxx because direct Deck "
"outputs are affected by Mixxx’s internal ones."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:203
msgid "**Midilog 1:** This strip controls Deck 3/C"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:204
msgid "**Midilog 2:** This strip controls Deck 1/A"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:205
msgid "**Midilog 3:** This strip controls Deck 2/B"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/american_audio_vms4.md:206
msgid "**Midilog 4:** This strip controls Deck 4/D"
msgstr ""
